me.utk.util.misc

Class Verify

  • java.lang.Object
    • me.utk.util.misc.Verify

  • public abstract class Verify
extends Object
    An abstract utility class for verification functions.

    This class provides these methods:

    • The isTrue methods, which throw an IllegalArgumentException if and only if the given boolean expression evaluates to false.
    • The isFalse methods, which throw an IllegalArgumentException if and only if the given boolean expression evaluates to true.
    • The isNull methods, which throw an IllegalArgumentException if and only if the given object expression is not null.
    • The isNotNull methods, which throw an IllegalArgumentException if and only if the given object expression is null.
    Version:
    January 3, 2020
    Author:
    Utkarsh Priyam
    See Also:
    Verify

      • isNotNull

        public static void isNotNull(Object obj)
        Throws an IllegalArgumentException if and only if the given Object argument is not not-null or equivalently is null.

        If an exception is thrown, it is initialized with a null message.

        For a method with identical functionality that returns the argument as well, use Objects.requireNonNull(Object) instead.

        Parameters:

        Throws:
        IllegalArgumentException - If the Object argument is null
        See Also:
